steps.description:
${echo}

Ok, now imagine we are 15 minutes into the future and you no longer have this problem.

How great it would be to have all this free time and money, not to mention be free of the symptoms?

${echo}

Great, that's usually the case.

Now let's proceed to the next step

Now in a moment, I’ll have you watching yourself on the other side of ${s21}, as ${he} is touching the similar stimulant - ${s18} - having a perfectly appropriate healthy response.

Again, go for full (even exaggerated) contact. See ${him} touching it, playing with it, rubbing it fully, with hands, body, and face, really getting ${himself} all over it.

As you watch ${him} really getting into it, start holding the anchor we established earlier:

${s19}

And keep it holding it, until I tell explicitly you to let go.

Ready?

Here are the steps to recap:
1. See yourself on the of the side of ${s21}
2. Watch ${him} touching the similar stimulant: ${s18}
3. As you see ${him} really getting into it, start holding the anchor we established earlier: ${s19}
4. Keep holding the anchor until I explicitly tell you to let go

You can do this with eyes open or closed, and click the button below when you’re done (while still holding the anchor)

Do it now.

Next I’ll orient you back a couple of steps, to where you are watching yourself having an appropriate response to the similar stimulant: 

${s18}

Afterwards, you will again watch yourself playing with a cat, and this time make the adjustments and changes in your response to your liking.

He -> ${he}  
Him -> ${him}  
his -> ${his}
